definitions.definition: a small room in which a prisoner is locked up or in which a monk or nun sleeps.
examples: room, cubicle, chamber; Moredungeon, oubliette, lockup "a prison cell"Moredungeon, oubliette, lockup a prison cell

definitions.definition: a small monastery or nunnery dependent on a larger one.

the smallest structural and functional unit of an organism, typically microscopic and consisting of cytoplasm and a nucleus enclosed in a membrane. Microscopic organisms typically consist of a single cell, which is either eukaryotic or prokaryotic.
an enclosed cavity in an organism.
examples: compartment, cavity, hole, hollow, section each cell of the honeycomb

definitions.definition: a small compartment in a larger structure such as a honeycomb.
examples: compartment, cavity, hole, hollow, section each cell of the honeycomb

definitions.definition: a small group forming a nucleus of political activity, typically a secret, subversive one.
examples: the weapons may be used to arm terrorist cells

definitions.definition: the local area covered by one of the short-range transmitters in a cellular telephone system.

examples: I'll just call him on his cell

definitions.definition: a device containing electrodes immersed in an electrolyte, used for current-generation or electrolysis.
a unit in a device for converting chemical or solar energy into electricity.
